Package: outcrossSimulator
Title: Simulate Outcross Breeding
Version: 0.0.0.01
Authors@R: 
    person("Daniel", "Gatti", , "dan.gatti@jax.org", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package allows the user to create a breeding population of a specified number of breeding pairs comprised from a specified number of inbred founders. It was designed for diploid organisms. It creates a breeding funnel from a randomized ordering of the founders and produces a pair of G2-F1 mice for each funnel. A population of breeding pairs can be created in this manner and then be fed into the outcrossing algorithm. We use the xoi R package to estimate the number and position of crossovers from each transmitted chromotid at each generation. We provide functions to aggregate allele frequency, crossovers, and inbreeding at each generation. 
